"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody, I want to talk about something that's affecting all of us in some way or another. Autoimmune disorders. Most of us are affected by them personally, either that you're suffering from them or someone you know and love is suffering from them. And this is something that is happening to all of us. It is everywhere in our culture. We treat this with medicines, but that just takes us back. We're actually destroying our immune system by trying to limit its effect on it slowly killing us. And that's what an autoimmune disorder is. It's a an imbalance in the immune system where healthy tissue is being attacked and unhealthy tissue is being left unattacked. That it's basically healing things that don't need to be healed and not healing the stuff that needs to get healed. It's a huge stress on the body. And a lot of this, in my opinion, is caused by the microflora in the gut. And the best way to fix this condition is to eat living rich in biology foods like raw fruits and vegetables and fermented foods from living soils. And it seems like a lot. But in my opinion, we have to reconnect our biome to the world. We've been eating sterilized food that has its biology removed, its connection to the world removed for so long that we thought this was a good idea, we thought this was safe, and now we're all ending up with biomes that are lacking the diversity they need to preserve our structures. And we're slowly getting dumb bacteria and it's killing us. And it's killing us more and more rapidly. And I have fear that there is a wave that's going to come, an epidemic of autoimmune disorders. And in my opinion, the only way to really solve this epidemic is to start eating real living foods again. And so I'm committed to my garden where I'm trying to get bacteria-filled calories. I'm trying to get a world within my food to help my world adjust to the most toxic environment that's ever existed. Anyway, thanks y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"te